news.title: China widens commercial property loan uses to ease liquidity
news.para: According to a notice jointly issued by the central bank and the financial regulator, by the end of this year banks will be able to provide commercial property loans to eligible developers to allow them to pay off debts that are not necessarily related to the project pledged as collateral.

news.title: China Evergrande's unit to sell entire stake in asset to cut debt
news.para: Hengda Real Estate Group Yuedong, a unit of the property giant, holds a 65% stake in Shantou Hengmeng, with the rest being held by Redleaf Trading, its Australia-based joint venture partner.

news.title: Facing shortage, Chandigarh administration plans 500 houses for government staff
news.para: Around 150 houses are planned under the police housing in Dhanas, 200 general houses in Sectors 43 and 46. For meeting this demand, the available land parcels, and existing old housing will be tapped into.

news.title: Madras HC takes serious view of unauthorised constructions, seeks reports from civic bodies
news.para: A division bench of Justice D Krishnakumar and Justice R Vijayakumar observed that several petitions had been filed before the court particularly for removal of unauthorised constructions or constructions put up with deviation of the approved plan.

news.title: Send notices to 64 illegal Arambol buildings in 15 days: Bombay HC
news.para: ​The court directed Goa Coastal Zone Management Authority (GCZMA) to issue show-cause notices within 15 days to 64 illegal structures and dispose of them in three months.

news.title: Illegal construction rampant, Ludhiana civic body seals eight unauthorised shops
news.para: The building branch officials of the civic body zone-C sealed eight shops which were established illegally on Loh-Langar land near Rudra enclave.

news.title: NBCC to develop mixed-use project worth Rs 2,000 crore in Kerala
news.para: The Kerala state government has approved the development of a 17.9-acre land parcel at Marine Drive, Kochi by the Kerala State Housing Board. The Rs 2000 crore project will involve the phased development of a mixed-use commercial and residential complex on a self-sustainable model.

news.title: Mangalam group to invest Rs 150 crore in a commercial project in Jaipur
news.para: Manglam Group is expected to register sales of Rs 200 crore by 2024 from this project. With 75% of the project area already booked, Manglam Signature Elite has received interest from both locals and investors from nearby cities.

news.title: Bengaluru: Unauthorised construction halted around Haralur Lake
news.para: Prompt action from citizens and intervention by the Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike (BBMP) have temporarily halted the unauthorised construction, shedding light on the urgent need for a comprehensive survey of the lake’s boundaries.

news.title: Over 20,000 properties sealed in a day in Ahmedabad
news.para: The highest number of properties, 6,025, was sealed in the North Zone.

news.title: Borivli civic market to be redeveloped into multi-storeyed green building
news.para: While the ground-plus-first floor will be used for current licensees, the complex is also likley to house a parking lot and municipal staff quarters apart from commercial space, which will be leased out.

news.title: Karnataka HC will monitor Karanth layout in Bengaluru
news.para: A special division bench comprising Justices Krishna S Dixit and M Nagaprasanna noted that the SC’s December 12 order left it to the wisdom of the high court to continue the committee.

news.title: Despite Bombay HC order, 109 families stuck in Mhada red tape
news.para: The Parvati building redevelopment project has remained stagnant for 13 years, leaving the affected families not only homeless but also devoid of the transit rent promised by the developers.

news.title: DLF acquires 29 acres land in Gurugram for Rs 825 crore
news.para: DLF directly or through its affiliates, intends to acquire overall rights and interest in land parcel admeasuring ~29 acres having estimated development potential of upto 7.5 million sq ft.

news.title: EaseMyTrip co-founder buys office space in Gurugram for Rs 99 crore
news.para: According to documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, the acquisition of as done in November last year and the executive has paid Rs 6.95 crore stamp duty for the transaction.

news.title: NCLT admits Piramal Capital's insolvency plea in Rs 1,065-crore default by developer
news.para: The Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal has also appointed Jayesh Natvarlal Sanghrajka as the resolution professional for the company.

news.title: Noida: No water in Panchsheel Hynish for a week, residents go to kin
news.para: Residents said they visited their friends and relatives as there was no water in their washrooms and kitchens. On Thursday, they discussed the matter with the district magistrate.

news.title: Bollywood writer, director Krishna DK buys duplex for Rs 35.50 crore in Mumbai
news.para: As part of the deal, the buyers will also get ownership rights to a 1.62% land parcel of the Tower Windsor Grande Residences, which also counts other Bollywood personalities, including actors and leading singers, as apartment owners.

news.title: Investment opportunities V exits PNB Housing; sells entire stake for Rs 2,106 crore
news.para: ​According to the block deal data available with the BSE, Investment Opportunities V Pte Ltd offloaded more than 2.56 crore shares, amounting to a 9.88 per cent stake in PNB Housing Finance.

news.title: China regulator urges banks to grant financing for property projects
news.para: Financial institutions should not blindly withdraw and cut off loans for eligible property projects that have encountered temporary difficulties on construction, Xiao Yuanqi, deputy director of the NFRA, said at a news conference.
